Sharodotsav Pandit Nandan Mehta: Plan fo.details:
 The scheme &amp;quot;Sharodotsav Pandit Nandan Mehta: Plan for Conducting Classical Music Competition and Ceremony&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to preserve and promote the rich heritage of classical music and percussion through a state-level competitive platform dedicated to the memory of the legendary percussionist Pt. Nandan Mehta. A three-day classical music and percussion competition is held every year on February 26, the death anniversary of Pt. Mehta, where outstanding artists are recognized and awarded monetary prizes for their exceptional performances. The scheme is implemented by the Gujarat State Sangeet Natak Academy.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Late Jaswantsinhji Thakor and Late Rasik.details:
The scheme &amp;quot;Late Jaswantsinhji Thakor and Late Rasiklal Andhariya Classical Music Scholarship&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to preserve and promote classical music in Gujarat by offering financial support to eligible Gurus for imparting training and to their disciples for receiving it. The scheme facilitates a 10-month classical music training period where selected Gurus can train up to 2 disciples, and both Gurus and disciples receive monetary assistance. The scheme is implemented by Gujarat Rajya Sangeet Natak Akademi, Gandhinagar, which releases a public advertisement annually inviting applications.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Scheme of Awarding Eklavya Award, Sardar.details:
The &amp;quot;Scheme of awarding Eklavya Award, Sardar Patel Award and Jaidipsinhji Award&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth, and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat aims to recognize and incentivize the outstanding achievements of sportspersons by providing financial rewards across senior and junior categories based on their performances at state, national, and international levels. The scheme is implemented by the Sports Authority of Gujarat.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Publication Support Scheme for Fine Arts.details:
 The scheme &amp;quot;Publication Support Scheme for Fine Arts&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to increase awareness about fine arts and promote the publication of fine arts literature by supporting artists and art institutions financially. Under this initiative, applications are invited annually through paid newspaper advertisements, and 2 (two) artists/art institutions are provided assistance for the publication of fine arts books.. The scheme is implemented by the Gujarat State Fine Arts Academy.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Girnar Arohan-Avrohan Competition.details:
 The scheme “Girnar Arohan-Avrohan Competition” by the Department of Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities, Government of Gujarat, aims to encourage physical endurance, sports participation, and cultural spirit among individuals by organizing an annual state-level stair-climbing competition on Mount Girnar. Out of the 9,900 steps of the mountain, the competition mandates male participants to complete 5,500 steps and female participants to complete 2,200 steps. Participants who secure positions among the top 10 are rewarded with substantial cash prizes, thereby motivating individuals of all backgrounds to embrace physical challenges and celebrate Gujarat’s heritage.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Uttarakhand Rajya Shilp Ratna Puraskar.benefits:
  - Every year, 25 artisans from the state of Uttarakhand are honored with the &amp;quot;Uttarakhand Rajya Shilp Ratna Puraskar.&amp;quot; 
  - Each selected outstanding artisan receives a cash prize of ₹1 lakh, along with a memento (symbolic representation), an angavastra (ceremonial stole) and a certificate of appreciation.

<br>

Shaktidoot Scheme.details:
The &amp;quot;Shaktidoot Scheme&amp;quot; Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Gujarat, is designed to nurture promising athletes in Gujarat by providing resources to help them excel in sports. The scheme focuses on developing champions by offering need-based assistance, including nutritious food, advanced sports facilities, modern equipment, competition expenses, expert trainers, psychological workshops, and sports medicine. Financial aid varies based on the athlete’s potential, achievements, and the level of competition they participate in. Additional provisions include medical coverage and accidental death insurance.
&lt;br&gt;

&lt;br&gt;

Tanariri Music Awards Festival and Award.details:
The scheme &amp;quot;Tanariri Music Awards Festival and Awards (National Level)&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to commemorate the legacy of legendary musical artistes Beldi Tana and Riri and promote the cultural heritage of Indian classical music by honoring two exceptional female artistes from across the country. These artists are felicitated at a prestigious national-level award ceremony held at Vadnagar, Gujarat, with a cash prize of ₹5,00,000, a shawl, and a certificate each.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Rock Climbing Adventure Training Course.details:
The scheme &amp;quot;Rock Climbing Adventure Training Course&amp;quot; by the Sports, Youth and Cultural Activities Department, Government of Gujarat aims to develop a spirit of adventure, encourage physical endurance, and boost confidence and discipline among children belonging to Scheduled Tribes through a structured training program. The scheme provides selected students with an opportunity to participate in a 6-day residential rock climbing adventure course conducted at either Mount Abu or Junagadh. It focuses on holistic development by engaging youth in outdoor sports activities, thereby fostering physical and mental growth.
&lt;br&gt;

<br>

Nirmaan Shramik ke Bachchon Hetu Utkra.details:
Labor Department of Chhattisgarh State started this scheme &amp;amp;quot;Nirmaan Shramik  Ke Bachchon Hetu  Utkrasht Khel Protsaahan Yojana&amp;amp;quot; for Construction Workers on 23 May 2017. The main objective of the scheme to provide financial to encourage the studdents for sports.
&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;

Financial Assistance For Promotion Of Gu.details:
The Ministry of Culture, Government of India, launched the scheme “Financial Assistance for Promotion of Guru-Shishya Parampara (Repertory Grant).” Under this scheme, financial assistance will be provided to dramatic groups, theatre groups, music ensembles, children&amp;#39;s theatre, and all genres of performing arts activities.
&lt;br&gt;

The Ministry of Culture will evaluate the grantees through periodical inspections, field visits, etc., as may be necessary for the scheme on a periodical basis. As regards the fresh cases of this scheme, the approved grant in each case shall be released only after physical verification of the Organisations as decided by the Ministry. Further, a minimum of 5-10% of new recommended proposals/cases would be physically inspected/verified by the Officers concerned in the Ministry of Culture.
